body:
### Describe the bug

I tried to build pyarrow with the 3.0b1 release of cython.  I received some errors that I do not receive with earlier versions (0.29.x) of cython.

### Code to reproduce the behaviour:

```cython
    @property
    def dim_names(self):
        return tuple(frombytes(x) for x in tuple(self.stp.dim_names()))
```
[(source)](https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/main/python/pyarrow/tensor.pxi#L554-L556)


Supplementary definitions:

```cython
# self.stp.dim_names() calls this C++ function (defined elsewhere in a pxd):
const vector[c_string]& dim_names()
```

`frombytes` is probably not relevant but it converts a C++ string to a python str.



### Expected behaviour

I expect the function to build fine and return a list of strings.

### OS

Linux

### Python version

3.11.0

### Cython version

3.0b1

### Additional context

